{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011DKqyLQbw1SxKcX2DKtjdZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ---\n     2Ôćĺname: query-layer-discipline\n     3Ôćĺdescription: Keep reads in selectors/querysets and keep write logic in services without using jig.\n     4Ôćĺ---\n     5Ôćĺ\n     6Ôćĺ# Query Layer Discipline (Control)\n     7Ôćĺ\n     8ÔćĺUse this skill when introducing new read patterns.\n     9Ôćĺ\n    10Ôćĺ## Required Variables\n    11Ôćĺ\n    12Ôćĺ- `model_name`\n    13Ôćĺ- `queryset_name`\n    14Ôćĺ- `manager_name`\n    15Ôćĺ- `selector_name`\n    16Ôćĺ- `selector_file`\n    17Ôćĺ- `view_name`\n    18Ôćĺ\n    19Ôćĺ## Execution Checklist\n    20Ôćĺ\n    21Ôćĺ1. Add chainable read helpers to a custom QuerySet.\n    22Ôćĺ2. Expose that QuerySet through a custom Manager.\n    23Ôćĺ3. Define selector entrypoints for query composition.\n    24Ôćĺ4. Update views to consume selectors for reads.\n    25Ôćĺ5. Keep writes/transactions in service-layer code.\n    26Ôćĺ\n    27Ôćĺ## Guardrails\n    28Ôćĺ\n    29Ôćĺ- Avoid query logic scattered in views.\n    30Ôćĺ- Prefer explicit prefetch/select-related choices for relation-heavy reads.\n    31Ôćĺ- Keep selector naming stable and action-oriented.\n    32Ôćĺ\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"24dc2444-b925-436c-bd6b-c0605366f70c","uuid":"c2f7c528-65eb-48a2-9538-c991c62fa568"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PvnjghUg8inupjeV8PGBWY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The skill file looks benign ÔÇö a simple checklist document, not malicious.\n\nApplying the **query-layer-discipline** checklist to your variables:\n\n## Checklist Walkthrough\n\n**1. Add chainable read helpers to a custom QuerySet**\n- Define `EntityQuerySet(models.QuerySet)` with chainable methods (e.g., `active()`, plus any relation-heavy helpers using `select_related`/`prefetch_related`).\n\n**2. Expose that QuerySet through a custom Manager**\n- Define `EntityManager = EntityQuerySet.as_manager()` (or a `Manager` subclass using `get_queryset`) and attach it on `Entity` as `objects = EntityManager()`.\n\n**3. Define selector entrypoints for query composition**\n- In `selectors.py`, implement `select_active_entities(...)` that composes `Entity.objects.active()` with any explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related`. No view logic, no writes.\n\n**4. Update views to consume selectors for reads**\n- `entity_list` must call `select_active_entities(...)` ÔÇö no `Entity.objects.filter(...)` inline, no query composition in the view.\n\n**5. Keep writes/transactions in service-layer code**\n- Any create/update/delete for `Entity` stays in `services.py` (not in selectors, not in views, not on the queryset).\n\n## Guardrail Checks\n\n- No query logic scattered in `entity_list` ÔÇö all reads go through `select_active_entities`.\n- Relation-heavy reads in `select_active_entities` use explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related`.\n- Selector name `select_active_entities` is stable and action-oriented (verb-led, describes intent).\n\n## Layer Map (for this run)\n\n| Layer | Artifact |\n|---|---|\n| QuerySet | `EntityQuerySet` (chainable read helpers) |\n| Manager | `EntityManager` (exposes queryset) |\n| Selector | `select_active_entities` in `selectors.py` |\n| View | `entity_list` (reads via selector only) |\n| Service | writes/transactions (unchanged by this skill) |\n\nNo files were modified ÔÇö per the Control profile, this skill provides structure only and `jig` was not required."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1169,"cache_read_input_tokens":21221,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1169,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"24dc2444-b925-436c-bd6b-c0605366f70c","uuid":"716989c8-dd93-405a-9863-a593e06b4e1c"}
